---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Now";
const description = "What I'm up to currently";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="space-y-10 text-foreground">
    <!-- Dark panel header -->
    <header
      class="relative overflow-clip rounded-xl bg-[oklch(0.11_0_0)] px-6 py-8 dark:ring-1 dark:ring-white/5 sm:px-8 sm:py-10"
    >
      <div
        class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-8 -top-8 size-48 rounded-full blur-2xl"
        style="background: radial-gradient(circle, oklch(0.72 0.18 42 / 0.2), transparent 65%);"
        aria-hidden="true"
      ></div>
      <div class="relative">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
          Now<span class="text-rf-accent">.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-1 text-white/50">{description}</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="divide-y divide-foreground/10">
      <!-- February 2026 -->
      <article class="pb-10 first:pt-0">
        <header
          class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-foreground/10 pb-4"
        >
          <h2 class="font-serif italic text-3xl text-foreground sm:text-4xl">
            February<span class="text-rf-accent">.</span>
          </h2>
          <span class="font-mono-custom text-sm text-foreground-muted">2026</span>
        </header>

        <div class="space-y-3 py-6 text-foreground-muted">
          <p>
            I just returned from my first company offsite which took place in
            Portland, OR. It was a long week but great to meet everyone in-person
            and get to know everyone better.
          </p>
          <p>
            During February, I plan to continue my focus on my mental and
            physical health including returning to the gym which I'm excited for.
            I'm also focusing a lot on my finances this year to prepare to move
            into a new apartment next year. The plans are made, now it's up to me
            to execute.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm also excited for a handful of projects I'm working on, one of
            which is a personal dashboard I can use to track various things like
            my social following, habits, to-dos, and more. Think of it like a
            one-stop-shop for myself.
          </p>
          <p>
            More on that will be shared in the near-ish future on my <a
              href="https://x.com/ryandotfurrer">X/Twitter</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-foreground/10 pt-5">
          <p class="small-heading mb-3 text-rf-accent">Currently</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-foreground-muted">
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Watching</span> · Finishing
              up <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uXr9Ha9qRHE"
                >Dan Da Dan (Season 2)</a
              > → Rewatching <a
                href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Iwr1aLEDpe4"
                >Frieren: Beyond Journey's End, S1</a
              > before <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EOMVXqH9DSg"
                >Season 2</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Reading</span> · <a
                href="https://store.dailystoic.com/collections/all-books/products/the-obstacle-is-the-way-expanded-10th-anniversary-edition"
                >The Obstacle is the Way</a
              > by Ryan Holiday
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Playing</span> · <a
                href="https://www.expedition33.com/"
                >Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Obsessing over</span> · <a
                href="https://youtu.be/KsrN_jsDFOA?si=dRT_Mg1ffS_CYfIG"
                >Radiohead's "Creep" by Erin Morton</a
              > and <a href="https://youtu.be/9WoCqEZMBL0?si=Olk9GyCHzv2VywOW"
                >"New York, New York" by Lawrence</a
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- January 2026 -->
      <article class="py-10">
        <header
          class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-foreground/10 pb-4"
        >
          <h2 class="font-serif italic text-3xl text-foreground sm:text-4xl">
            January<span class="text-rf-accent">.</span>
          </h2>
          <span class="font-mono-custom text-sm text-foreground-muted">2026</span>
        </header>

        <div class="space-y-3 py-6 text-foreground-muted">
          <p>
            Focusing on both my mental and physical health, giving it all at my
            job, and moving into a new apartment next year. I'm setting up the
            systems now to help me stay on track and meet my goals.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-foreground/10 pt-5">
          <p class="small-heading mb-3 text-rf-accent">Currently</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-foreground-muted">
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Watching</span> · <a
                href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uXr9Ha9qRHE"
                >Dan Da Dan (Season 2)</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Reading</span> · <a
                href="https://store.dailystoic.com/collections/all-books/products/the-obstacle-is-the-way-expanded-10th-anniversary-edition"
                >The Obstacle is the Way</a
              > by Ryan Holiday
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Playing</span> · <a
                href="https://www.expedition33.com/"
                >Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Obsessing over</span> · <a
                href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jH3xpS7Q_3E&list=OLAK5uy_k_hE5HhMiwlHuzdS7R17Yk8w68ilnSrMw&index=2"
                >Final Fantasy VII Remake Acoustic Arrangements</a
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
